  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Fighters/Bombers and Torpedoes<o:=
p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Caleph are flying Reptiles, large creatures that=
 can
  have up to <span class=3DGramE>a 15 meters</span> wing span. The Caleph v=
ary in
  size, with more subtle variations in color and looks. The different
  variations in the species rarely interbreed. Partially due to this, the
  Caleph have developed a strong caste-based society, with groups defined by
  physical characteristics that, to the outside observer, might seem too su=
btle
  to warrant differentiation.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Because of their natural ability for flight the Cale=
ph are
  used to dealing and navigating in three-dimensional space. They make
  extremely good pilots and in space combat they are unequalled in ability.=
<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Their natural flight ability has allowed the Caleph =
to
  develop a different type of fighter bay, the All-Dimension Fighter Bay, t=
his
  allows them to hold and repair fighters much more efficiently. The Caleph
  have also developed their own fighter craft that are paragons of
  maneuverability.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Caleph seek out hot places for their homes. They do =
not
  have houses or habitats like most races might--they claim tracts of land =
as
  &quot;homes.&quot; Additionally, this can be as a family or pack--less of=
ten
  as an individual.</p>
